g.title: EleanorRank3Convo4 begins.
g.text: EleanorRank3Convo4 begins.

g.title: j2758303613
g.text: So stop me if I get any of this wrong:

g.title: j928674755
g.text: You’ve got another self out there, walking around. That other self both is and isn’t you. They’re like a kid version of you from another version of reality.

g.title: j3895114118
g.text: Not quite. This is their version of reality. I’m the outsider here.

g.title: j3947310451
g.text: More like we split at some point, I took a left turn, they went right.

g.title: j3016955504
g.text: Whoa Nelly. Hang on. Let me process that.

g.title: j3246908716
g.text: And I take it we are in THEIR reality, not yours. Let me... process that.

g.title: j3208539348
g.text: So… you’re like a guest star from a crossover episode and you got written into the show?

g.title: j2477522718
g.text: Pretty much.

g.title: j756255198
g.text: This is making my head spin. So what happened to your version of reality? Where’s it gone?

g.title: j1483700870
g.text: I think the only thing left of it is the ghost ship Zariman plugging a hole between dimensions...?

g.title: j842455441
g.text: I think whatever was left of it came with me into Duviri. For...better or worse.

g.title: j1021068877
g.text: I don’t dwell on that much. I guess it’s lost.

g.title: j622483262
g.text: Check boolean EleanorHoldfasts1

g.title: j1527882775
g.text: Then it lives on, in some sense.

g.title: j1865837584
g.text: You can’t just LOSE a whole cosmos. That’s insane. It has to be out there somewhere.

g.title: j4223566358
g.text: Ah! The lair of your friendly ghosts. The Holdfasts.

g.title: j622483262->j4223566358
g.text: true

g.title: j3758730938
g.text: I'm sorry, that sounds fascinating but I have no idea what you're on about.

g.title: j622483262->j3758730938
g.text: false

g.title: j3010877946
g.text: I don't know if that's any kind of a comfort.

g.title: j62992498
g.text: It might be. Like I said, not my major concern.

g.title: j2970753066
g.text: I can't imagine it's the kind of place you'd want to pop back to for a nostalgic stroll.

g.title: j406120917
g.text: Ghost ship?

g.title: j4181875286
g.text: I've learned that home, and family, is more about what you make of the "where" and the "who" around you.

g.title: j4071468641
g.text: But that’s your HOME. Don’t you want to get back there?

g.title: j88252316
g.text: I can't begin to fathom what you've lost.

g.title: j4224075124
g.text: Hole between dimensions?

g.title: j4264733212
g.text: Less about where and what you're born into.

g.title: j4263965822
g.text: It’s really not, not anymore. I don’t really have a home.

g.title: j768257280
g.text: I don't see it that way.

g.title: j2931155856
g.text: The Zariman was the colony ship I was on. Headed for Tau. Never made it.

g.title: j3823298812
g.text: I don't focus on what was lost. I focus on what I still have. Like this place. Like all of you. Because...

g.title: j2273869776
g.text: The ‘Drifter’ nickname stuck for a reason, you know.

g.title: j614601872
g.text: I made it out. I survived. How insanely lucky is that?

g.title: j2961449648
g.text: She ended up in the Void, and something that existed there decided to turn the ship into a vision of hell.

g.title: j3870561039
g.text: Of all the places I’ve been, this feels most like where I belong.

g.title: j1899930558
g.text: Honestly, the odds of any one of us actually existing in the first place are so slim, it's just one more miracle to me.

g.title: j1555835024
g.text: She's been washing back and forth from the Void to reality, and now she's stuck on the threshold.

g.title: j2220312449
g.text: Huh. I’m oddly proud of that.

g.title: j388024657
g.text: Don't focus on what was lost. Cherish what we've got.

g.title: j3001571325
g.text: She's not really one ship, either. She's like... lots of different versions at once.

g.title: j1304069747
g.text: Maybe you just needed the right bunch of lethally stylish urban bio-commandos to associate with.

g.title: j3709540102
g.text: For example? I have this place now. And all of you. It's the first place I've ever really had that feels like home.

g.title: j721535401
g.text: Boolean EleanorHoldfasts1 is now true.

g.title: j1300999584
g.text: Misfits and screwups like me?

g.title: j94015421
g.text: I can't imagine it's the kind of place you'd want to pop back to for a nostalgic stroll.

g.title: j571227994
g.text: And proud of it, mate.

g.title: j988699594
g.text: I can't begin to fathom what you've lost.

g.title: j4204265641
g.text: But getting back to the other version of you…

g.title: j1629649887
g.text: I don't see it that way.

g.title: j488340918
g.text: I have this place, now. The first place I've ever really had that feels like home.

g.title: j2378362400
g.text: Right. Ordis calls them ‘the Operator’. Lotus calls them her child. Mostly I just call them the kid.

g.title: j3437833056
g.text: I try to avoid them as much as I can. I don't get paid enough to babysit, even if it is just me.

g.title: j4118460234
g.text: I made it out. I survived. How insanely lucky is that?

g.title: j4061780858
g.text: +10 Chemistry

g.title: j3737967984
g.text: Ooh. Harsh.

g.title: j1639941360
g.text: Honestly, the odds of any one of us actually existing in the first place are so slim, it's just one more miracle to me.

g.title: j3978629636
g.text: Check boolean EleanorLotus

g.title: j3614355376
g.text: Given how much you have in common, you might be a little kinder.

g.title: j2840257648
g.text: I love that she has children. Lethal space children.

g.title: j3978629636->j2840257648
g.text: true

g.title: j2668771429
g.text: So here’s the part I don’t understand.

g.title: j3978629636->j2668771429
g.text: false

g.title: j1104188673
g.text: I wonder if she'd let me be one? Do I get to be a Tenno?

g.title: j3071125934
g.text: The kid is umpty-billion years old, but they spent most of that time in a freezer, so they’re still a kid, right?

g.title: j1036911469
g.text: No. I don't suppose I would, would I? I'm too old, for a start.

g.title: j3660920389
g.text: Something like that.

g.title: j693074748
g.text: Not sure how "childlike" they really are when they've been trained to murder for a living.

g.title: j3672094900
g.text: Okay.

g.title: j1767680628
g.text: A. Child. Is. A Child.

g.title: j3580258543
g.text: Bear with me.

g.title: j515372541
g.text: They don't conveniently turn into something else when they're mistreated.

g.title: j1105601990
g.text: Stop me immediately if this isn’t something you want to talk about.

g.title: Chat ends.
g.text: Chat ends.

g.title: j3083035583
g.text: The Zariman? What happened with your parents? This child has been through the same horrific ordeal you went through, right?

g.title: j3457809559
g.text: Yes.

g.title: j807921489
g.text: You have to understand there was only the one of me, of us, at first. We were exactly the same person, right up to the moment where I shook that thing’s hand. That’s when they went their way and I went mine.

g.title: j1840983125
g.text: Okay. My head hurts thinking about it, but okay.

g.title: j738746623
g.text: So there’s a child. A profoundly traumatized child. And someone thought it was a good idea to give this child weapons and armour and a selection of battle suits made from dead people, train them to kill, and send them off to war?

g.title: j3145640617
g.text: Yup. That was the Orokin.

g.title: j4205171621
g.text: Tell me, after everything they’ve been through and are still going through, how is that child not catatonic in a hospital?

g.title: j287063411
g.text: Honestly, I couldn’t tell you. I know they’ve got people who love them and look out for them. Ordis and Lotus, mainly.

g.title: j1162956771
g.text: Void knows they’ve seen way more violence and bloodshed than any kid ever should. They never signed up for this shit, either.

g.title: j674738706
g.text: The Tenno didn’t get a choice about being made into warriors. The Orokin were going to kill every one of them before they found a use for them.

g.title: j34268809
g.text: But what keeps them going inside? I don’t think that’s something they were trained to do. It’s something about who they are.

g.title: j2036073204
g.text: Caring? Empathy?

g.title: j2820185617
g.text: Justice. Righteousness.

g.title: j304918870
g.text: Something deeper, maybe.

g.title: j415295389
g.text: Survival instincts. People want to live, at the end of the day.

g.title: j3862202944
g.text: Check boolean EleanorHeroVirus

g.title: j3468268029
g.text: Whatever the opposite of Indifference is, perhaps.

g.title: j3068917090
g.text: Hmm. I don't know.

g.title: j1431928663
g.text: Of course. The Hero Virus. I should have known it would survive to your time.

g.title: j3862202944->j1431928663
g.text: true

g.title: j3611290757
g.text: Ugh. The Hero Virus.

g.title: j3862202944->j3611290757
g.text: false

g.title: j2789868075
g.text: I wonder…

g.title: j4040330449
g.text: They'd be no different to the Techrot if all they wanted to do was survive.

g.title: j3437612586
g.text: Those poor kids were steeped in a myth, weren't they?

g.title: j1568636365
g.text: That's what I call the cycle of bullshit that starts with pretty stories and ends with young people willingly going to their deaths.

g.title: j3505461213
g.text: What?

g.title: j2034338951
g.text: The way you talk about the kid, I'm not sure if I'm more scared for them or of them.

g.title: j2597224598
g.text: Trained to believe they were honourable warriors, not innocent catspaws?

g.title: j3313455380
g.text: Arthur has it. Christopher had it.

g.title: j1610030338
g.text: Nothing. Just an idea.

g.title: j3513071503
g.text: I think there's mercy in there, though. Some deep compassion. Maybe one day I'll see it for myself.

g.title: j1015887651
g.text: No need to answer. I think I already know.

g.title: j537808543
g.text: Maybe I can develop a vaccine and save history.

g.title: j4151030310
g.text: This is going to sound stupid, but please promise me something.

g.title: j4081414586
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j679405944
g.text: Boolean EleanorHeroVirus is now true.

g.title: j2790302020
g.text: I know you’ve found a place here with us. I’m glad about that, truly.

g.title: j2300696250
g.text: All I ask is that you check on the child, if you can.

g.title: j3827329980
g.text: The child is fine, honestly. Lotus is with them. So’s Loid. They’re not about to break down.

g.title: j3957330673
g.text: Don’t underestimate them, Eleanor. They did just fine without me for years.

g.title: j1370391797
g.text: Don’t worry. I’m already doing that. I’ll tell them you said hello, if you like.

g.title: j3170180011
g.text: Okay. I just hope you're sure.

g.title: j2591666542
g.text: I'm not sure that slaughtering thousands while carrying untold trauma is 'doing fine', frankly.

g.title: j1886753200
g.text: Thank you. I admit, the idea of talking to an alternate version of yourself is exciting to me.

g.title: j3498166905
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j1678999526
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j3106748003
g.text: Check boolean EleanorSister

g.title: j3674340515
g.text: Because whatever they have inside them that can endure everything they went through and still feel empathy? We're going to need it.

g.title: j405799539
g.text: I'd want to know how they were coping.

g.title: j3074858577
g.text: I’ve been trying to make contact with her telepathically. If you can do it so can I, right?

g.title: j3106748003->j3074858577
g.text: true

g.title: j1668377508
g.text: In fact, learning of your alternate version convinced me there must be another me out there somewhere who decided to become a nun. An apostle of Lua, shaven head, regular prayers, all of that.

g.title: j3106748003->j1668377508
g.text: false

g.title: j2044857591
g.text: I’m not sure that’s such a great idea.

g.title: j542599649
g.text: Have you gotten anywhere?

g.title: j2682779739
g.text: Boolean EleanorSister is now true.

g.title: j2542320023
g.text: Don't be such a spoilsport.

g.title: j870422230
g.text: No. But I’m going to keep trying.

g.title: j3641528173
g.text: I mean if anyone’s going to have words of wisdom for me it’ll be the me who’s been devoting her life to spiritual things, no?

g.title: j368990542
g.text: +10 Chemistry

g.title: j3042548382
g.text: Let’s hope so.

g.title: j1539045688
g.text: If you're sure...
